## Summary

This room introduces Hydra, an online brute-force tool used to automate password guessing against live services. Two attacks were performed against the target: a HTTP POST form brute-force to compromise a web login, and an SSH brute-force to gain shell access. Both used the `rockyou.txt` wordlist and a known username (`molly`).

## Tools Used

- `hydra` — online brute-force / password cracking
- `ssh` — remote shell access
- `rockyou.txt` — password wordlist (`/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt`)

