## Task 1 — Hydra Introduction

No flags. Theory only.

Hydra automates credential guessing against live services. It supports many protocols including SSH, FTP, HTTP, HTTPS, SMB, and more.

**General syntax:**
```bash
hydra -l <username> -P <wordlist> <IP> <service>
```

Key flags:

| Flag | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `-l` | Single username |
| `-L` | Username list |
| `-p` | Single password |
| `-P` | Password list |
| `-t 4` | Limit threads (important for SSH) |
| `-V` | Verbose — show each attempt |

